[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and consent, cross-organizational data integration with longitudinal-store assembly, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with clinical-emergency screening, identity-and-context loading with cross-system reconciliation, conversation handling with care-coordination-grounded responses and action authorization, output safety screening with action-confirmation and citation discipline, action execution and tracking with closed-loop discipline, warm handoff to human care managers when applicable, and audit logging with cross-organizational retention discipline. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (cross-system data integration as architectural primitive, authoritative-source-of-truth precedence rules, action-authorization matrix, care-transition discipline, closed-loop tracking discipline).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CONSENT ──────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via plan, provider, or hospital        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-management program]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to care-coordination     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      AI interaction                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-organizational data-sharing consent            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Action-scope consent (which actions may bot take     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      autonomously, which require human)                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team-sharing consent (which providers may       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      receive bot-generated updates)                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Authorized-representative consent where the patient  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      has a family caregiver or surrogate                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Privacy posture explained in plain language          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed consent record; enrollment confirmation]│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CROSS-ORGANIZATIONAL INTEGRATION ──────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Activate data feeds across organizations]              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Provider EHRs (potentially multiple)                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Payer claims and authorization systems               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pharmacy fill data                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Lab and imaging vendors                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Home-health agency records                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Post-acute facility records                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Durable-medical-equipment vendors                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scheduling systems                                   │
