[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Handoff targets]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active emergency: 911 with stay-on-the-line          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care manager queue: standard handoff                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Specialty care manager (behavioral health, social    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      work, etc.) where appropriate                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Specific clinician where the question is clinical    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and the clinician relationship is authorized         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Warm-handoff payload]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent conversation transcript                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reconciled longitudinal context                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-journey summary                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open loops and their states                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent transitions of care                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trigger reason and confidence signal                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient preferred contact method                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot's structured proposal where applicable           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bridge-and-stay pattern]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot bridges to care manager within the platform      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot stays present until care manager has joined      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient does not start over                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: handoff event with structured payload]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND POST-LAUNCH MONITORING ────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User and bot turns                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care-coordination-playbook version            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active plan-benefits-content version                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Care-coordination-specific retention discipline]       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific medical-record rules,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      cross-organizational data-sharing-agreement          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      retention specifications, and any litigation-hold    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      obligations                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-organizational audit trail accessible to       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      each contributing organization for their own         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      compliance purposes                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Closed-loop rate by loop type                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Transition-of-care follow-up rate                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-completion rate                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Authorization-turnaround time                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-handoff completion rate                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-augmentation efficiency                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (caseload extension, time-saved per case)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      flags, plan, organization)                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as multi-quarter to multi-year     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    commitment]                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Readmission-rate effects                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - ED-utilization effects                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-plan-adherence effects                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-experience effects                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-manager-workforce effects                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of high-risk      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      conversations, escalations, and stuck-loop cases     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (registered nurses with care-management    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      experience) tag failure modes (out-of-scope,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clinical-decision-attempted, action-authorization-   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      violation, citation-gap, reconciliation-error,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      data-sharing-overreach, tone-failure, equity-        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      disparity)                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-coordination-playbook revisions driven by       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      review findings                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    playbook-revision proposals]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system data integration as architectural primitive.** The bot reads from many organizations. Each integration has its own data-sharing agreement, authentication, reliability profile, latency budget, and audit trail. The integration layer is a first-class architectural component, not an afterthought.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Authoritative-source-of-truth precedence rules.** When data conflicts across systems, institutional precedence rules govern reconciliation. The reconciled view is what the bot presents; conflicts are surfaced to the human care manager.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Action-authorization matrix as architectural primitive.** Each action has scope (autonomous, propose-to-human, out-of-scope), authorization (consents, clinician approval), and audit. The matrix is institutionally specified and reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and legal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-transition discipline as launch-blocker.** Transition-of-care windows are highest-risk. The bot's transition support is a launch-gate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Closed-loop tracking discipline as architectural primitive.** Each ordered service has a lifecycle. The bot tracks open loops, surfaces stuck loops, reports closed-loop rates as operational metric.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Operational integration with the human care-manager workforce.** The bot is a force-multiplier, not a replacement. Workflow integration into care-manager tooling, queue, and escalation pathway is required.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-organizational data-sharing posture.** Reviewed by counsel familiar with cross-organizational health-information-sharing law including HIPAA, 42 CFR Part 2, state-specific protections, 21st Century Cures Act information-blocking rules, TEFCA frameworks where applicable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every coordination response grounded in cited source (institutional content or longitudinal data) with version preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Caregiver-versus-patient discipline.** Bot identifies who is typing (patient or authorized caregiver) and applies appropriate consent posture and tone.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, closed-loop rates, transition-of-care follow-up rates, and outcomes vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, plan, and contributing organization. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and equity teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any cross-organizational integration is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. Minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble reaching that system right now; let me connect you with your care manager" with direct routing to human support. Per-source failover is documented and tested quarterly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
